  • Classes in com.googlecode.gwt.charts.client used by com.googlecode.gwt.charts.client 
    Class and Description
    BoundingBox
    Represents the boundaries of a box, defined by left, top, width and height.
    ChartEditor
    The ChartEditor class is used to open an in-page dialog box that enables a user to customize a visualization on the fly.
    To use ChartEditor: Load the ChartPackage.CHARTEDITOR package.
    ChartLayoutInterface
    Represents an object containing information about the onscreen placement of the chart and its elements.
    ChartObject
    Represents a generic chart javascript object with all common methods.
    ChartPackage
    A definition of available packages.
    ChartType
    A definition of currently available chart types.
    ChartWrapper
    A ChartWrapper class is used to wrap your chart and handle all loading, drawing, and Datasource querying for your chart.
    ChartWrapperObject
    A ChartWrapperObject class is used to wrap your chart and handle all loading, drawing, and Datasource querying for your chart.
    ChartWrapperSpec
    A ChartWrapperObject initializer specification as described in google.visualization.drawChart().
    ColumnFunction
    An interface for providing a calculated function to a DataViewColumn.
    ColumnRange
    Represents the minimal and maximal values of values in a specified column.
    ColumnType
    Data type of the values of a DataTable column.
    DataCell
    Represents a cell object for adding to a DataTable.
    DataColumn
    Represents a column object for adding to a DataTable.
    DataLiteral
    You can initialize a DataTable by passing a JavaScript string literal object into the data parameter.
    DataRow
    Represents a row object for adding to a DataTable.
    DataSource
    This class implements the common methods of DataTable and DataView.
    DataTable
    Represents a two-dimensional, mutable table of values.
    DataView
    A read-only view of an underlying DataTable.
    DataViewColumn
    Represents a calculated column.
    DateRange
    Represents a date range.
    HasListeners
    This class provides event support like described in Chart Events.
    Most visualizations fire events to indicate something has occured.
    Properties
    A common name/value map, tipically applied to tables, rows, columns or cells.
    RoleType
    A column role describes the purpose of the data in that column: for example, a column might hold data describing tooltip text, data point annotations, or uncertainty indicators.
    RowFilter
    Each filter is an object with a numeric column property that specifies the index of the column in the row to assess, plus one of the following:
    A value property with a value that must be matched exactly by the cell in the specified column.
    Selection
    A representation of a selection in a chart.
    SortColumn
    Represents an object for sorting a DataTable.
    TimeOfDay
    Representation of time of day that may be used as a value in a data table (or data view).
